<h2 id="blog">Embodiment of the Idea</h2>

<p id="blog">  I imagined an enclosed stretcher with a power supply and lift motors capable of carrying a patient from the point of injury to a treatment facility.  In one embodiment, twin turbogenerators power four lift motors and an auxiliary battery pack to provide lift capabilities.  The auxiliary pack augments the turbine power output to provide instant power demands which might not be met by an accelerating turbine.</p>

<!-- patent isometric -->
 <img class="articleImage" src="http://res.cloudinary.com/x78163/image/upload/v1505691387/Patent_3_bvd0mt.jpg" alt="" />

<p id="blog"> The patient lies on a stretcher, strapped in place to protect them during flight.  A suite of biosensors are applied to their body, along with additional monitoring devices or treatment devices (AED, etc.).  As more automated treatment devices emerge, these would be incorporated into the vehicle.  The patient's vitals are monitored via a datalink by the treatment facility, allowing the providers to thoroughly assess the patient prior to admission.   </p>

