<p id="blog"> The aircraft would use a triple redundant autopilot to navigate to the location.  It would automatically plot the flight path using the latest map data and use machine vision to clear the landing site.  It maintains provisions for external operators to change the flight path or over-ride the navigation (in case the patient must be diverted to another facility). </p>

<!-- extended -->
 <img class="articleImage" src="http://res.cloudinary.com/x78163/image/upload/v1505691387/Patent_1_hjkgcd.jpg" alt="" />

<p id="blog">  It communicates over whatever communication infrastructure suits the operator's need.  Cellular networks for civil use, military TCDL for combat roles or SATCOM for remote site employment.  The system services subscribers, or system users through the system network.  Just like Uber, a subscriber can request a vehicle dispatched.  The system prioritizes the requests based upon urgency, distance and other factors.  It then identifies the closest aircraft and passes the destination to the flight computer.  On consent from a human supervisor, the aircraft conducts its preflight and launches towards the point of injury.</p>

