<p id="blog"> Upon returning to the treatment facility, the aircraft presents the patient to the care team.  When taken, the aircraft then returns to the launch site for refueling, maintenance and resupply.  Once complete, the aircraft is released back into the available pool for the system to dispatch again as needed.</p>

<h2 id="blog">Building it!</h2>
<p id="blog"> Well, you can have an idea on paper....but it is way more fun to have an idea in the flesh.  Granted, I am no Daddy Warbucks, so I had to keep this on a shoestring budget.  Also, my neighbors would have lost their mind if I built a twin turbine drone in my garage.  </p>
<br>

<p id="blog"> I started by identifying some of the key components.  I found the Hololens system to be a great way to prototype.  While the videos show it finicky, it was actually quite nice while modeling to have reference graphics available at all times. </p>
